{"id":4686,"title":"Extraction of total RNA from E. coli cells","title_html":"<p>Extraction of total RNA from <em>E. coli<\/em> cells<\/p>","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.gtnbwme","doi_status":2,"uri":"extraction-of-total-rna-from-e-coli-cells-gtnbwme","type_id":1,"published_on":1585148208,"parent_protocols":[],"parent_collections":[],"cited_protocols":[],"version_id":0,"created_on":1482145747,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Alice Pawlowski","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[{"affiliation":null,"url":null,"is_default":1}],"username":"alice-pawlowski","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/004.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/004.png"},"badges":[{"id":3,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg"},"name":"Power author!"},{"id":5,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/earlyadopter.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/earlyadopter.svg"},"name":"Early adopter"}],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"article_citation":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":"","total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":4,"authors":[{"name":"Alice Pawlowski","affiliation":"Institute of Synthetic Microbiology, CEPLAS, Heinrich Heine University Duesseldorf","affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"is_owner":1,"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"fork_id":null,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"88D2E6C8B9DA11E99CA40242AC110005","state_version_id":1387,"steps":[{"id":231477,"guid":"CB3CF5C0DF7744839026A7E975EAA291","previous_id":900976,"previous_guid":"2E9467506CF011EA95E355C38B4C0109","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"26D63A901E68445ABDD84A2995AD69D3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"stop of RNA synthesis"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6E12C07FF3654CADA4A15D884BD5158F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">work under the hood<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">mix 1 ml of cells with 200 \u00b5l 'stopmix'- solution (5 % phenol in ethanol)\u00a0in a 2 ml safe lock tube tube \u2192 stops RNA production in the cells<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">centrifuge for 5 min at 4\u00b0C and 14000 x g<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">discard the supernatant and resuspend the pellet in 1 ml\u00a0NucleoZOL (Macherey and Nagel),\u00a0\u00a0place on ice (better for rapid freezing: dry ice or liquid nitrogen)<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\u2192 store cells at -20 or\u00a0\u00a0-80 \u00b0C (only for a short time, maximum 2 weeks)  or proceed to next step<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":231973,"guid":"BA91DB0AC3E64665A78A0DD4EE8E8D66","previous_id":231477,"previous_guid":"CB3CF5C0DF7744839026A7E975EAA291","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"10187D691F194A82998F570978BD1C6D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA-isoloation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"70930B30404642AF86BDE769EB8D5B3F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">incubate the sample at 65 \u00b0C and 250 rpm (Thermomixer) for 10 min<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">mix with 400 \u00b5l Phenol-Chloroform\/Isoamylalcohol (Roti\u00ae-)Aqua-P\/C\/I) by inverting for 10 s<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">centrifuge at 4\u00b0C for 10 min at 14000 x g<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">transfer aqueous (upper) phase to a fresh 1,5 ml safe lock reaction tube, work on ice<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">mix with 450 \u00b5l Chloroform\/Isoamylalcohol (Roti\u00ae-C\/I)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">centrifuge at 4\u00b0C for 10 min at 14000 x g<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">transfer aqueous (upper) phase to a new reaction tube and add 1 Vol. icecold Isopropanol + 1\/10 vol (e.g. 20 \u00b5l for 200 \u00b5l Isopropanol) 3 M Na-Acetat (pH 5.2), mix and store at least 30 min at\u00a0 -20 \u00b0C or -80 \u00b0C<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">centrifuge at 4\u00b0C for\u00a030 min at 14000 x g<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">remove the supernatant (take care of the RNA-pellet) and add 350 \u00b5l of icecold 75% Ethanol<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">centrifuge for 5 min at 4\u00b0C and 15000 rpm<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">add again 350 \u00b5l of icecold 75% etahnol and centrifuge for 5 min at 4\u00b0C and 15000 rpm<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">remove the supernatant and dry the pellet at room temperature for ca.15 min<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">resuspend\u00a0 the pellet in 30\u00a0\u00b5l Molecular Biology Grade Water and store at -80\u00b0C<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":237228,"guid":"4CD5AF08A9F74CF9A8E4F23148174466","previous_id":231973,"previous_guid":"BA91DB0AC3E64665A78A0DD4EE8E8D66","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E118231E598A44A7B3DD82D97A3773D0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8851DD0BC8364CF394DF18934AED2F7F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":900976,"guid":"2E9467506CF011EA95E355C38B4C0109","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"514334E22C214A3A8FA69B1FC1FB7E2D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"incubation of cells "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C253DDF83AAC4F869F37810E5B5480A6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>freshly transform <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli <\/span><span>cells with plasmids encoding trRNA sequences or empty vector<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">inoculate 3 ml LB-vegetal medium + antibiotic (25 \u00b5g\/ml Km for W1310, 25 \u00b5g\/ml + 100 \u00b5g\/ml Spec for W1310Z1) in culture tubes with a single colony<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">incubate o\/n at 37\u00b0C and 230 rpm<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>for constitutive RNA-synthesis (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span> W3110): <\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">dilute 1:100 in fresh medium with 25 \u00b5g\/ml Km and incubate until OD600 reaches 0.7 - 1.0 (in culture tubes or 6 well plates), proceed to step 2<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>for induced RNA-synthesis (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span> W3110Z1): <\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">dilute 1:50 in fresh medium ( 200 \u00b5l o\/n culture in 10 ml medium + antibiotic in 100 ml Erlenmeyer flask) and incubate until OD600 reaches 0.4 - 0.6<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">if you have several different cultures that do not grow at same speed: store samples on ice until the last one reaches the defined OD (keep that one on ice as well for 10 min)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">meanwhile prepare 12 well plates with inducer: pipet in each well of a row 10 \u00b5l of either <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        1) EthOH, <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        2) aTC (= 200 ng\/ml final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        3) IPTG ( = 100 \u00b5M final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        4) aTc + IPTG ( 200 ng\/ml, 100 \u00b5M final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">add 1 ml of culture and incubate at 37\u00b0C and 230 rpm for 1 h<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">proceed with step 2<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>for constitutive RNA-synthesis (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span> W3110): <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">dilute 1:100 in fresh medium with 25 \u00b5g\/ml Km and incubate until OD600 reaches 0.7 - 1.0 (in culture tubes or 6 well plates), proceed to step 2<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>for induced RNA-synthesis (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span> W3110Z1): <\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">dilute 1:50 in fresh medium ( 200 \u00b5l o\/n culture in 10 ml medium + antibiotic in 100 ml Erlenmeyer flask) and incubate until OD600 reaches 0.4 - 0.6<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">if you have several different cultures that do not grow at same speed: store samples on ice until the last one reaches the defined OD (keep that one on ice as well for 10 min)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">meanwhile prepare 12 well plates with inducer: pipet in each well of a row 10 \u00b5l of either <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        1) EthOH, <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        2) aTC (= 200 ng\/ml final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        3) IPTG ( = 100 \u00b5M final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        4) aTc + IPTG ( 200 ng\/ml, 100 \u00b5M final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">add 1 ml of culture and incubate at 37\u00b0C and 230 rpm for 1 h<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">proceed with step 2<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>for induced RNA-synthesis (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span> W3110Z1): <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">dilute 1:50 in fresh medium ( 200 \u00b5l o\/n culture in 10 ml medium + antibiotic in 100 ml Erlenmeyer flask) and incubate until OD600 reaches 0.4 - 0.6<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">if you have several different cultures that do not grow at same speed: store samples on ice until the last one reaches the defined OD (keep that one on ice as well for 10 min)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">meanwhile prepare 12 well plates with inducer: pipet in each well of a row 10 \u00b5l of either <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        1) EthOH, <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        2) aTC (= 200 ng\/ml final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        3) IPTG ( = 100 \u00b5M final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">        4) aTc + IPTG ( 200 ng\/ml, 100 \u00b5M final concentration)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">add 1 ml of culture and incubate at 37\u00b0C and 230 rpm for 1 h<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">proceed with step 2<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        1) EthOH, <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        2) aTC (= 200 ng\/ml final concentration)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        3) IPTG ( = 100 \u00b5M final concentration)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        4) aTc + IPTG ( 200 ng\/ml, 100 \u00b5M final concentration)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">add 1 ml of culture and incubate at 37\u00b0C and 230 rpm for 1 h<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">proceed with step 2<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":nul