ocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The protocol is used for the extraction of total RNA from <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span> cells. It is based on the method described by Chomczynski and Sacchi, 1987 (<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1016\/0003-2697(87)90021-2\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;:UNDERLINE;\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1016\/0003-2697(87)90021-2<\/span><\/a><span style = \":UNDERLINE;\">). <\/span><span>Total RNA is isolated from cells expressing small regulatory RNAs (trRNAs) either constitutively (E. coli W3110) or after induction with anhydrotetracycline (E. coli W1310 Z1). <\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1585148208}